[1mDESCRIPTION[0m[m
       [4mxxd[24m creates a hex dump of a given file or standard input.  It can also convert a hex dump[m
       back to its original binary form.  Like [1muuencode[0m(1) and [1muudecode[0m(1) it allows the  trans-[m
       mission  of  binary  data in a `mail-safe' ASCII representation, but has the advantage of[m
       decoding to standard output.  Moreover, it can be used to perform binary file patching.[m
[m
[1mOPTIONS[0m[m
       If no [4minfile[24m is given, standard input is read.  If [4minfile[24m is specified as a  `[1m-[0m'  charac-[m
       ter, then input is taken from standard input.

If no [4moutfile[24m is given (or a `[1m-[0m' character[m
       is in its place), results are sent to standard output.[m
[m
